features.text: 'Nikolina Petolas'With elements of subtle allegory, Nikolina expresses her eerie visions by guiding a viewer on a journey through her fictional worlds. Her profound detailed compositions have been recognized by Salvatore Ferragamo, as well as private collectors worldwide and luxury venues such as Seabourn & Marriot autograph collection. Nikolina's work has gained multiple international awards and has been exhibited globally, in galleries and museums of Europe, USA & Asia.

Lisa Odette is a 3D, 2D artist and animator who loves to explore the female essence through shapes and colors. With a Graphic Design background, she focuses on creating pleasing and eye catching compositions, always trying to fill the space in a balanced way. The design aspect can be also perceived in the outfit and pattern design that accompanies the characters in her pieces.

kolahon means chaos in Thai. The name came from a book that changed my life, "try to reinventing yourself in a chaotic world" had changed the way that I saw the world, the main concept is talking about the expression of the chaotic thought and diary it as a picture Dreams, freedom, yin - yang symbolize finding balance in life. it the signal that reminds the fragile self and tells a story with character design

Shir Pakman is a 3D illustrator based in Tel Aviv. She graduated from Bezalel Academy of Arts and Design, as an Animation Major and currently works as a 3D illustrator, designer, and Animator. Her work mixes both classical art and 3D illustration techniques to create unique artworks that walk between 2D and 3D art.

Tania Rivilis (b. 1986) - Russian-German contemporary self-taught artist 
(began painting at the age of 27). Artist’s physical works are presented on the Arcadia Gallery NYC, Galerie Bonnard (Netherlands), Urban Zen Donna Karan´s Studio NYC studio as well as on http://1stdibs.com and http://artsy.com. In April 2021 Tania started her NFT journey by transferring oil paintings into NFTs.

Sahred Toy Illustrator,Painter BKK,Thailand I'm an illustrator and doing general art. whether to paint or make toys and also working on writing I have been working for about 10 years. I grew up in a country of many faiths. Here molded me into who I am now. As you can see from the work I do. The stories that go through life are gradually conveyed into a work packed with lots of detail and fun colors. I want people to see the event and jump into the chaotic world. In my twisted imagination

When I was a small child, I wasn’t so happy At school I didn’t have many friends, I got bullied by people, and I didn’t have much toys to play with because we didn’t have enough money for our living after that I grew a bit bigger I knew about Japanese manga, The first manga Ive read was Dragon balls , I was so surprised I’ve found Another world that I’ve never seen it in the real world. That was when I knew about imaginary world. Finally I felt in love with them. I stared to draw and tried to create my world, I drew what I wanted to see in the world. And I called it 3land 3LAND” is My imaginary world In 3LAND, there are hundreds of funny and crazy monsters living in peace, with love and in adventures! When I was a small child, I would go to 3Land to play with my monsters. They were my best friends, and we went everywhere together. I remember flying our spaceship to outer space, going underwater in our submarine, and building a huge tree house in the jungle. 3Land has always been my playground. We never needed to fight because we knew we had everything enough for everybody in 3Land. In that magical world, you only have to picture what you want in your brain, and there you go. You can create anything, however impossible it may look, in this land. Art gives me live and It makes alive Imagination is magical. It s boundless. It is powerful. And it is playful. Enjoy the adventure!

Rishiraj is concept artist from India currently living in Sweden, he like to recreate and tell modern internet stories with his illustrations and taking inspiration from renaissence artists He is working in video game industry from 8+ years and he is with Ubisoft from last 6 years working as concept artist on many games.
